Everything seems fine for now.

265
00:23:46,029 --> 00:23:48,400
They should be careful
not to run into the infected.

266
00:23:50,099 --> 00:23:53,670
Doctor, I'll go check the generator.

267
00:23:53,740 --> 00:23:55,769
Sure, go ahead.

268
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:08,220
Hey, all the infected here disappeared!

269
00:24:08,990 --> 00:24:12,160
(Muji Hospital, 2nd Floor)

270
00:24:27,740 --> 00:24:29,410
Is there no other way to get there?

271
00:24:30,140 --> 00:24:31,440
Hold on.

272
00:24:33,440 --> 00:24:34,640
Can you hear me?

273
00:24:35,210 --> 00:24:36,750
Yes, this is the security room.

274
00:24:37,349 --> 00:24:38,420
Let me see.

275
00:24:38,619 --> 00:24:40,579
If you turn to the corner
from where you are,

276
00:24:40,650 --> 00:24:43,490
there's an emergency staircase
at the end of the corridor on the left.

277
00:24:43,549 --> 00:24:45,259
There's no one there.

278
00:25:45,279 --> 00:25:47,680
- It's too dangerous to leave now.
- Let me go.

279
00:25:47,750 --> 00:25:49,220
- No, you can't.
- Look!

280
00:25:49,819 --> 00:25:52,660
The smoke is gone,
and I can't see the infected.

281
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,619
How long should I stay here?

282
00:25:54,690 --> 00:25:56,930
Whether it's an army base or another city,

283
00:25:56,990 --> 00:25:58,529
we must do something.

284
00:25:58,599 --> 00:26:01,160
Darn it, you're so noisy.

285
00:26:01,230 --> 00:26:02,329
Look here.

286
00:26:03,529 --> 00:26:06,970
They say they want to leave,
why are you stopping them for?

287
00:26:07,799 --> 00:26:09,809
Let me get some sleep, will you?

288
00:26:10,539 --> 00:26:12,579
My kid and my wife are waiting for me.

289
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:15,009
You expect me to stay here and do nothing?

290
00:26:15,079 --> 00:26:18,210
You can stay here. I'm going to leave.

291
00:26:18,619 --> 00:26:22,720
If there's anyone who wants to leave,
come with me.

292
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:24,390
Where will he go?

293
00:26:24,450 --> 00:26:26,289
- We can't leave yet.
- We shouldn't leave.

294
00:26:26,359 --> 00:26:27,519
I'm leaving too.

295
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:30,759
- Let's go.
- We're also leaving.

296
00:26:30,829 --> 00:26:32,130
Okay, let's go.

297
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:33,660
Dad.

298
00:26:37,069 --> 00:26:38,170
What are you doing?

299
00:26:39,769 --> 00:26:41,269
Where are you going?

300
00:26:43,039 --> 00:26:46,380
Dad. Don't go.

301
00:26:49,579 --> 00:26:50,779
Dad.

302
00:26:51,279 --> 00:26:53,480
Dad. Don't leave us.

303
00:26:54,579 --> 00:26:56,720
Please open the door.

304
00:26:57,420 --> 00:26:59,390
How can you leave alone?

305
00:26:59,460 --> 00:27:00,559
Let go.

306
00:27:01,559 --> 00:27:02,630
Let go of me!

307
00:27:06,059 --> 00:27:08,730
Honey! You can't leave us!

308
00:27:08,930 --> 00:27:11,500
Dad! Save me!

309
00:27:11,700 --> 00:27:13,500
- Dad.
- Be quiet.

310
00:27:13,569 --> 00:27:15,309
She's crazy. Everyone's watching.

311
00:27:15,369 --> 00:27:17,539
- Please take us with you!
- No.

312
00:27:17,609 --> 00:27:19,079
- You piece of trash!
- It's not what you think.

313
00:27:19,140 --> 00:27:20,480
How can you leave us?

314
00:27:20,539 --> 00:27:22,150
I'm not your husband!

315
00:27:23,579 --> 00:27:25,279
You'll all die if you go outside.

316
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:27,019
Who are you?

317
00:27:27,650 --> 00:27:28,920
Go ahead and leave.

318
00:27:30,789 --> 00:27:33,859
You'll be punished severely
if you don't do as I say.

319
00:27:35,660 --> 00:27:38,500
You can show them yourself.

320
00:27:40,630 --> 00:27:44,130
You lunatic.
What kind of shaman witchery is this?

321
00:27:44,730 --> 00:27:45,799
Let's go.

322
00:27:45,940 --> 00:27:47,799
- Let's go now.
- All right.

323
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:49,839
- Wait.
- I'm leaving voluntarily.

324
00:27:49,910 --> 00:27:51,170
- Don't go.
- Come on.

325
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:53,539
- Where is he going?
- What does he think he's doing?

326
00:27:53,609 --> 00:27:55,509
- Don't go.
- My goodness.

327
00:27:57,950 --> 00:27:59,150
He really left.

328
00:28:14,430 --> 00:28:16,400
What was that about? She's such bad luck.

329
00:28:16,970 --> 00:28:17,930
What?

330
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:21,700
It's nothing. Let's get going.

331
00:28:22,769 --> 00:28:25,309
He showed me everything.

332
00:28:59,980 --> 00:29:03,049
- Hey! Open the door!
- Get lost, you punk!

333
00:29:03,109 --> 00:29:05,619
- Open the door!
- Come on!

334
00:29:05,680 --> 00:29:07,119
Why won't it start?

335
00:29:07,180 --> 00:29:09,819
Open the door! Open it!

336
00:29:09,890 --> 00:29:12,289
Help me! Help me!

337
00:29:13,990 --> 00:29:15,089
Darn it.

338
00:29:15,390 --> 00:29:16,789
Why won't it start?

339
00:29:20,900 --> 00:29:22,730
- They're dead.
- Did they really die?

340
00:29:22,930 --> 00:29:24,029
My goodness.

341
00:29:24,099 --> 00:29:26,440
You were right.

342
00:29:26,500 --> 00:29:27,970
You said we'll all die if we go outside.

343
00:29:28,039 --> 00:29:29,109
And they did.

344
00:29:29,170 --> 00:29:31,609
- Yes.
- They should've listened to her.

345
00:29:31,670 --> 00:29:34,839
- That's so scary.
- What will we do?

346
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:38,309
- Poor them.
- He insisted on leaving.

347
00:29:38,380 --> 00:29:41,849
That shaman is going to make a bloodbath.

348
00:30:05,980 --> 00:30:07,940
- My goodness.
- Will you look at it?

349
00:30:08,279 --> 00:30:09,410
I'm sorry, sir.

350
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:13,079
The kids must've never hammered
a nail in their lives.

351
00:30:13,579 --> 00:30:16,450
You should've taught them well
if they're not good at it!

352
00:30:16,519 --> 00:30:18,289
Must I tell you everything?

353
00:30:18,349 --> 00:30:19,960
No, sir. I'm so sorry.

354
00:30:21,789 --> 00:30:23,390
Are you kidding me?

355
00:30:24,430 --> 00:30:26,329
Jin Seok, let go of this.

356
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:29,930
Mister, are you joking?

357
00:30:30,329 --> 00:30:32,940
You can have these pickles
all by yourselves.

358
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:34,799
Eat them. Eat them!

359
00:30:34,869 --> 00:30:35,869
Hey!

360
00:30:37,839 --> 00:30:40,410
What are you doing to a teacher?

361
00:30:42,849 --> 00:30:45,549
Do you still think I'm your student?

362
00:30:46,180 --> 00:30:48,950
Hey, you guys expelled me.

363
00:30:49,519 --> 00:30:52,289
Why are you acting like
a teacher when you expelled me?

364
00:30:52,359 --> 00:30:53,559
Hey, little boy.

365
00:30:56,789 --> 00:30:57,630
What?

366
00:30:57,690 --> 00:31:00,299
Why are you being a picky eater
if you're not a kid?

367
00:31:01,599 --> 00:31:05,369
Oh, I see. Are you acting up
because you're a cop?

368
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:07,440
Darn you.

369
00:31:15,750 --> 00:31:17,009
Hey...

370
00:31:19,079 --> 00:31:20,180
Enough.

371
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:37,000
Open your eyes.

372
00:31:51,279 --> 00:31:52,279
Get up.

373
00:32:02,890 --> 00:32:05,730
What? What are you all looking at?

374
00:32:26,349 --> 00:32:27,950
Grandma called you to eat.

375
00:32:28,150 --> 00:32:30,390
- Look over there. Do you see it?
- What?

376
00:32:30,490 --> 00:32:31,819
Over there.

377
00:32:32,819 --> 00:32:35,789
With that, we can play catch. Right?

378
00:33:00,950 --> 00:33:03,250
Do Yoon, you're so brave!

379
00:33:07,859 --> 00:33:08,859
You can do it!

380
00:33:46,759 --> 00:33:50,230
Hey! It's dangerous! Come back quick!

381
00:33:56,470 --> 00:33:57,470
Hey!

382
00:34:20,329 --> 00:34:21,199
Why did you do that?

383
00:34:21,230 --> 00:34:23,269
Don't you know what happens
if you inhale the smoke?

384
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:26,969
Tell me! Why did you go outside?

385
00:34:27,269 --> 00:34:29,369
To fight the infected...

386
00:34:29,409 --> 00:34:31,369
we need a gun.

387
00:34:31,909 --> 00:34:33,539
You're a cop.

388
00:34:38,309 --> 00:34:39,519
Wait.

389
00:34:52,630 --> 00:34:54,429
Your name is Do Yoon, right?

390
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:58,699
Wow, I'm impressed, Do Yoon.

391
00:34:58,769 --> 00:35:01,340
You were really brave.

392
00:35:02,769 --> 00:35:07,340
But you can't do
something like this ever again.

393
00:35:07,409 --> 00:35:08,510
All right?

394
00:35:11,079 --> 00:35:12,949
Why don't you go inside first?

395
00:35:12,980 --> 00:35:16,219
I need to talk to the detective.
We'll be right there with you.

396
00:35:17,090 --> 00:35:18,190
Do Yoon.

397
00:35:36,039 --> 00:35:38,210
You may be good at catching criminals.

398
00:35:38,909 --> 00:35:41,739
But it seems you're not good at
talking to children.

399
00:35:44,250 --> 00:35:46,150
What she did was reckless.

400
00:35:47,179 --> 00:35:48,849
She knows that too.

401
00:35:49,550 --> 00:35:51,920
She knew that,
but she went out risking everything...

402
00:35:51,989 --> 00:35:53,260
for you.

403
00:35:54,320 --> 00:35:56,489
Maybe it's not my place to say this but...

404
00:35:58,230 --> 00:36:00,199
Try not to shut people out.

405
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:04,400
Because right now,
we have to get through this together.

406
00:36:13,780 --> 00:36:15,980
First, I'll put tripe on a perilla leaf.

407
00:36:16,050 --> 00:36:19,280
Then put noodles on it. What next?

408
00:36:19,650 --> 00:36:21,280
- Garlic.
- Right, garlic.

409
00:36:21,349 --> 00:36:22,889
- Then I'll wrap...
- Yes, make a wrap.

410
00:36:22,949 --> 00:36:24,150
And put it in my mouth.

411
00:36:24,849 --> 00:36:27,190
What are you, a pig?
Why would you eat my wrap?

412
00:36:27,260 --> 00:36:28,559
You kids know nothing about food.

413
00:36:28,619 --> 00:36:30,690
He even tried to steal my food earlier.

414
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:33,000
Haven't you heard about Ram-Don?

415
00:36:33,099 --> 00:36:36,269
Mix it with your right hand
and mix it with your left hand.

416
00:36:36,329 --> 00:36:39,170
That's Bibimmyeon commercial,
you ignorant pig.

417
00:36:40,869 --> 00:36:42,369
Darn it.

418
00:36:43,769 --> 00:36:46,880
Be quiet, little brats.

419
00:36:47,679 --> 00:36:50,480
What are you looking at? What do you want?

420
00:36:51,250 --> 00:36:52,849
Are you crazy, you little jerk?

421
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:55,550
Stop trying to intimidate us and get lost.

422
00:36:55,619 --> 00:36:57,449
You weren't so strong
in front of that detective.

423
00:37:02,289 --> 00:37:03,730
Have you all gone crazy?

424
00:37:03,789 --> 00:37:06,360
What? What do you want from us?

425
00:37:09,329 --> 00:37:12,340
Just wait and see what I'll do to you.

426
00:37:16,239 --> 00:37:19,139
He should be embarrassed.
Why are you up? Lie down.

427
00:37:19,380 --> 00:37:21,840
Should we just gang up on him?

428
00:37:21,909 --> 00:37:23,309
- Should we?
- Yes, let's.

429
00:37:23,380 --> 00:37:24,679
- Just be quiet.
- Darn it.

430
00:37:28,019 --> 00:37:31,889
Honey, why are you alone?
Where did your mother go?

431
00:37:32,719 --> 00:37:34,190
She's...

432
00:37:35,190 --> 00:37:36,559
not my mother.

433
00:37:38,429 --> 00:37:39,929
My mother is...

434
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:42,699
It's okay. It's okay.

435
00:37:43,269 --> 00:37:46,170
You don't have to say it. I know.

436
00:37:47,670 --> 00:37:50,110
Let's go get something to eat with Chang.

437
00:38:12,090 --> 00:38:13,360
What are you doing?

438
00:38:14,500 --> 00:38:15,869
You're having so much fun, aren't you?

439
00:38:17,130 --> 00:38:18,369
What are you talking about?

440
00:38:18,429 --> 00:38:20,440
You think you have something on me.

441
00:38:21,599 --> 00:38:22,909
Just tell them.

442
00:38:23,369 --> 00:38:25,440
Tell them and I'll kill everyone.

443
00:38:25,510 --> 00:38:26,880
I told you before.

444
00:38:27,380 --> 00:38:29,349
Tell me how you're going to kill me.

445
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:36,289
A creative way to kill me.

446
00:38:37,219 --> 00:38:39,119
Tell me if anything pops into your head.

447
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:43,960
But I doubt your stupid head
will come up with one.

448
00:39:22,699 --> 00:39:25,800
Do Yoon! Listen to the detective.

449
00:39:25,869 --> 00:39:28,239
Make sure you survive. Okay?

450
00:39:29,369 --> 00:39:33,440
Detective! Just go now!

451
00:39:36,510 --> 00:39:38,179
My mom...

452
00:39:38,809 --> 00:39:42,320
always found me wherever I hid.

453
00:39:45,860 --> 00:39:47,360
It's okay now.

454
00:39:56,670 --> 00:39:58,000
It's cold at night.

455
00:39:59,300 --> 00:40:00,699
Thank you.

456
00:40:05,340 --> 00:40:07,940
Children easily become friends.

457
00:40:09,750 --> 00:40:12,349
I'm sure you'll be a good friend to her.

458
00:40:15,849 --> 00:40:19,989
I don't know how to treat her.

459
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:27,329
When I look into her eyes,
I can see how desperate she is.

460
00:40:28,860 --> 00:40:31,070
But I'm not sure if I can protect her.

461
00:40:32,230 --> 00:40:33,570
I'm scared.

462
00:40:35,739 --> 00:40:36,969
Well...

463
00:40:37,639 --> 00:40:40,110
What she wants from you right now...

464
00:40:41,179 --> 00:40:42,340
is...

465
00:40:43,250 --> 00:40:46,280
just being there for her.

466
00:40:47,250 --> 00:40:50,849
So don't try too hard to do something.

467
00:41:19,349 --> 00:41:20,449
What was that?

468
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,179
Quiet down.

469
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:28,860
This is Doctor Han.

470
00:41:31,130 --> 00:41:32,130
Yes.

471
00:41:32,190 --> 00:41:34,960
There's an emergency exit
at the cardiovascular center.

472
00:41:35,099 --> 00:41:37,400
It seems like the fastest way.

473
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:39,670
Yes. Got it.

474
00:41:51,780 --> 00:41:55,119
(Muji Hospital, 3rd Floor)

475
00:41:59,719 --> 00:42:00,989
The power of authority.

476
00:42:16,610 --> 00:42:19,909
(Muji Hospital, 4th Floor)

477
00:42:49,539 --> 00:42:50,940
What is it?

478
00:42:55,639 --> 00:42:57,510
I think it's nothing.

479
00:42:58,409 --> 00:42:59,719
Let's move.

480
00:43:00,050 --> 00:43:02,380
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

481
00:43:03,750 --> 00:43:07,559
I should stay strong
for the sake of my baby.

482
00:43:17,500 --> 00:43:18,500
Wait.

483
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:20,800
Look at that.

484
00:43:22,099 --> 00:43:24,110
Why are they going that way?

485
00:43:26,139 --> 00:43:28,010
Isn't that the 4th floor?

486
00:43:29,510 --> 00:43:30,909
The negative pressure room.

487
00:43:30,980 --> 00:43:32,610
The smoke can't get in the room there.

488
00:43:32,679 --> 00:43:34,280
They're going to the negative
pressure room because it's safe.

489
00:43:35,219 --> 00:43:36,250
Can you hear me?

490
00:43:36,320 --> 00:43:39,460
People on the 5th floor... the 4th floor.

491
00:43:39,619 --> 00:43:41,059
Not the 5th floor...

492
00:43:43,329 --> 00:43:44,389
What is she saying?

493
00:43:44,690 --> 00:43:46,059
People on the 5th floor...

494
00:43:46,099 --> 00:43:48,159
are going to the negative pressure room
on the 4th floor.

495
00:43:48,230 --> 00:43:50,269
It's not the 5th floor, but the 4th floor.

496
00:43:52,800 --> 00:43:55,340
Can you hear my...

497
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:57,010
The 4th floor?

498
00:43:58,409 --> 00:43:59,780
Why the 4th floor?

499
00:44:00,409 --> 00:44:01,739
She said the 4th floor.

500
00:44:02,179 --> 00:44:03,610
Give me that.

501
00:44:05,780 --> 00:44:07,280
Say that again.

502
00:44:12,090 --> 00:44:13,989
Say that again.

503
00:44:14,059 --> 00:44:16,360
Officer Cho, can you hear my voice?

504
00:44:39,150 --> 00:44:40,380
What's wrong?

505
00:44:41,349 --> 00:44:46,590
Well, that jailer somehow looks familiar.

506
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:48,489
What do you mean?

507
00:44:51,059 --> 00:44:52,059
It's nothing.

508
00:44:52,829 --> 00:44:54,659
I must be on edge.

509
00:45:41,039 --> 00:45:42,039
Run!

510
00:46:16,409 --> 00:46:17,480
Get in quickly!

511
00:46:41,969 --> 00:46:43,969
See that? Authority.

512
00:46:46,480 --> 00:46:48,579
You should've shot earlier.

513
00:46:49,679 --> 00:46:51,150
I thought I was going to die!

514
00:47:16,869 --> 00:47:19,070
The ones who do not accept me will die.

515
00:47:20,280 --> 00:47:22,780
The ones who do not accept me will die.

516
00:47:23,349 --> 00:47:25,650
They shall all die.

517
00:47:25,880 --> 00:47:27,349
The ones who do not accept...

518
00:47:29,519 --> 00:47:30,789
shall die.

519
00:47:31,219 --> 00:47:33,559
The ones who do not accept me will die.

520
00:47:34,019 --> 00:47:37,559
The ones who do not accept me will die.

521
00:48:25,739 --> 00:48:27,309
Tell me what you want.

522
00:48:28,010 --> 00:48:29,510
I'll grant you your wish.

523
00:48:51,199 --> 00:48:52,769
Accept me.

524
00:48:54,340 --> 00:48:58,369
Then you can take revenge!

525
00:48:59,880 --> 00:49:00,940
Who are you?

526
00:49:02,440 --> 00:49:04,179
Why did you stop the attack?

527
00:49:04,579 --> 00:49:05,849
Because it's fun.

528
00:49:06,679 --> 00:49:09,179
I can toy with them however I like.

529
00:50:53,389 --> 00:50:54,690
Who on earth did this?

530
00:51:10,670 --> 00:51:11,670
Sir!

531
00:51:12,710 --> 00:51:15,380
Wake up! Are you okay? Sir!

532
00:51:16,010 --> 00:51:17,079
Sir!

533
00:51:18,610 --> 00:51:20,719
We should quickly take him to the shelter.

534
00:51:21,179 --> 00:51:23,449
We can't take him there.
Others will get scared.

535
00:51:23,849 --> 00:51:26,119
Then there's a consultation room.

536
00:51:26,190 --> 00:51:27,889
- Let's take him there.
- Okay.

537
00:51:28,619 --> 00:51:30,130
- Hurry up!
- My gosh.

538
00:51:30,190 --> 00:51:31,929
Hang in there.

539
00:51:31,989 --> 00:51:33,030
This way.

540
00:51:33,090 --> 00:51:35,400
Hurry up!

541
00:51:43,440 --> 00:51:44,440
Quickly.

542
00:51:45,070 --> 00:51:46,070
Hurry up.

543
00:51:48,539 --> 00:51:49,539
Here you go.

544
00:51:54,449 --> 00:51:56,079
Do you have any medicine for first aid?

545
00:51:56,150 --> 00:51:59,860
Medicine that can treat a wound
this bad is in the infirmary.

546
00:51:59,920 --> 00:52:02,420
We can't go to the annex.
There are too many of the infected.

547
00:52:02,489 --> 00:52:05,130
If he's not treated, he'll go into shock
from losing too much blood!

548
00:52:09,559 --> 00:52:10,900
I'll go.

549
00:52:12,369 --> 00:52:14,099
Just tell me where the infirmary is.

550
00:52:14,170 --> 00:52:16,239
But it's too dangerous to go to the annex.

551
00:52:17,670 --> 00:52:19,980
You two helped me as well,
despite the danger.

552
00:52:21,179 --> 00:52:22,280
What do you need?

553
00:52:22,809 --> 00:52:25,309
Surgical instruments to close the wound,
hydrocolloid dressing,

554
00:52:25,380 --> 00:52:28,480
bandages, painkillers,
and hydrogen peroxide.

555
00:52:28,550 --> 00:52:31,119
Please bring povidone and dry powder
just in case.

556
00:52:31,190 --> 00:52:33,920
Also, bring all the painkillers
and anti-inflammatory drugs you can find.

557
00:52:33,989 --> 00:52:35,059
Got it.

558
00:52:41,929 --> 00:52:42,929
Detective.

559
00:52:43,900 --> 00:52:46,329
Do you think
this is a civil defense drill?

560
00:52:48,469 --> 00:52:50,670
This is an actual situation!

561
00:52:51,369 --> 00:52:54,380
So stop running around
without my permission, got it?

562
00:52:54,539 --> 00:52:57,079
If he doesn't get treated fast,
he might die.

563
00:52:57,150 --> 00:52:59,179
Yes, he might die,

564
00:52:59,380 --> 00:53:02,880
and everyone else here would die because of you.

565
00:53:04,019 --> 00:53:07,219
I'm the owner of this school.
I'm the one in charge.

566
00:53:07,289 --> 00:53:11,329
I'm responsible
for the safety of the people here.

567
00:53:11,389 --> 00:53:13,130
You can't even take responsibility
for one person,

568
00:53:13,190 --> 00:53:15,130
so how can you take responsibility
for everyone?

569
00:53:15,800 --> 00:53:17,170
Isn't it strange?

570
00:53:17,730 --> 00:53:21,599
There's always that one bad apple...

571
00:53:21,670 --> 00:53:24,139
which spoils the whole barrel.

572
00:53:25,269 --> 00:53:26,980
- What?
- This is why...

573
00:53:27,809 --> 00:53:31,280
order and control are most important.

574
00:53:31,679 --> 00:53:34,880
We can't spoil the whole barrel
just because of one rotten apple...

575
00:53:34,949 --> 00:53:36,820
that came out of nowhere, can we?

576
00:53:38,590 --> 00:53:42,119
Tell me honestly. What do you really want?

577
00:53:45,360 --> 00:53:48,300
You can remain here under my authority,

578
00:53:48,360 --> 00:53:52,030
or you can go get the medicine...

579
00:53:52,099 --> 00:53:53,699
and leave the school.

580
00:53:59,170 --> 00:54:00,239
Fine.

581
00:54:00,840 --> 00:54:03,349
I'll leave the school
once I get the medicine.

582
00:54:03,409 --> 00:54:04,449
Detective.

583
00:54:04,510 --> 00:54:07,750
Oh, right. I forgot.

584
00:54:08,449 --> 00:54:10,989
Since you came with the kid,
you should take her too.

585
00:54:11,050 --> 00:54:14,119
That's enough, Father.
Anyone who leaves this place dies!

586
00:54:14,190 --> 00:54:17,289
Sacrifice is needed to save everyone else!

587
00:54:19,190 --> 00:54:20,730
Don't you agree?

588
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:25,469
Chairman Choi, isn't it too harsh
to kick out the kid?

589
00:54:28,170 --> 00:54:32,570
Then you should go outside instead.

590
00:54:36,949 --> 00:54:38,079
Dong Rim.

591
00:54:38,550 --> 00:54:41,519
Wow, Han Dong Rim.

592
00:54:42,880 --> 00:54:44,650
I have a plan.

593
00:54:45,090 --> 00:54:46,219
What do you mean?

594
00:54:46,289 --> 00:54:48,719
There's a way you can go to the infirmary
while avoiding the infected.

595
00:54:48,789 --> 00:54:50,260
You're out of your mind.

596
00:54:50,760 --> 00:54:52,030
Follow me.

597
00:54:56,559 --> 00:54:59,400
The quickest way to the infirmary
is to cross this overpass.

598
00:54:59,469 --> 00:55:00,639
(Overpass)

599
00:55:00,699 --> 00:55:02,139
But as we all fled here,

600
00:55:02,170 --> 00:55:04,369
we locked all the doors
to keep the infected out.

601
00:55:05,170 --> 00:55:06,409
What about the keys?

602
00:55:06,980 --> 00:55:09,780
Well, the teacher who had the keys...

603
00:55:11,409 --> 00:55:12,849
got infected.

604
00:55:13,679 --> 00:55:15,619
We can get there without the keys.

605
00:55:15,849 --> 00:55:18,320
- What?
- This door is broken.

606
00:55:20,190 --> 00:55:21,289
What are you doing?

607
00:55:21,360 --> 00:55:24,090
They were saying
the door wouldn't lock so I checked.

608
00:55:24,289 --> 00:55:25,929
And it seems I have to change the latch.

609
00:55:26,289 --> 00:55:27,960
Do you have to change the whole thing?

610
00:55:34,599 --> 00:55:37,539
Gosh, you guys are so frustrating.

611
00:55:38,070 --> 00:55:39,610
Why are you here?

612
00:55:42,840 --> 00:55:45,849
Well, I wanted to help.

613
00:55:45,909 --> 00:55:47,349
What do you really want?

614
00:55:48,949 --> 00:55:52,719
How can I just sit and watch
when a man is dying?

615
00:55:53,250 --> 00:55:55,090
I'm not that horrible.

616
00:55:55,219 --> 00:55:59,130
Besides, even if the door is open
like she said,

617
00:55:59,530 --> 00:56:02,500
how will you pass the study hall corridor?

618
00:56:03,130 --> 00:56:05,329
You don't know where
and how many infected there are.

619
00:56:05,400 --> 00:56:08,170
The three of you are
just going to fight through them?

620
00:56:10,909 --> 00:56:13,809
Are you saying you have another plan?

621
00:56:16,710 --> 00:56:20,820
Well, you know, I'm good with tricks.

622
00:56:22,179 --> 00:56:24,849
Then tell us what your trick is.

623
00:56:28,659 --> 00:56:32,059
Detective, are you
good at distracting others?

624
00:57:34,860 --> 00:57:35,960
Hey.

625
00:57:37,789 --> 00:57:39,630
- Do you hear me?
- What's this?

626
00:57:39,690 --> 00:57:41,030
Where is it coming from?

627
00:57:42,730 --> 00:57:45,469
- It's not from mine.
- Yes, Detective.

628
00:57:46,099 --> 00:57:49,800
I know it's hard to believe,
but I saw something in the smoke.

629
00:57:50,210 --> 00:57:52,570
The black smoke isn't the end of it.

630
00:57:53,639 --> 00:57:56,210
What do you mean
the black smoke isn't the end?

631
00:57:57,309 --> 00:57:58,909
Inside the black smoke,

632
00:57:59,550 --> 00:58:02,619
there's a being we do not know about.

633
00:58:03,280 --> 00:58:04,519
Be careful.

634
00:58:06,920 --> 00:58:09,159
Detective. Detective.

635
00:58:09,559 --> 00:58:11,929
Which detective? Who is it?

636
00:58:12,329 --> 00:58:14,000
She's a detective from Seoul.

637
00:58:16,329 --> 00:58:19,570
She clearly said there's something
inside the black smoke.

638
00:58:20,539 --> 00:58:21,599
What?

639
00:58:33,050 --> 00:58:36,420
(A day ago)

640
00:58:37,719 --> 00:58:39,219
We cleaned out his stomach,

641
00:58:39,289 --> 00:58:40,789
but we found pesticides.

642
00:58:41,219 --> 00:58:44,030
He can go home when he gets up
and after he's done with the IV.

643
00:58:59,070 --> 00:59:00,809
Hello, Chief. It's me.

644
00:59:01,579 --> 00:59:05,679
I think he drank pesticide. Yes.

645
00:59:06,510 --> 00:59:09,150
I'll get back to the station
once he's done with his IV.

646
00:59:29,139 --> 00:59:30,170
What of the emergency power?

647
00:59:30,239 --> 00:59:32,340
Check the vitals
of the patient in Room 503.

648
01:00:23,289 --> 01:00:24,530
Sir.

649
01:00:36,170 --> 01:00:37,170
(Exit)

650
01:00:49,750 --> 01:00:51,889
(We'd like to thank Lee Cheol Min
for his special appearance.)

651
01:01:08,570 --> 01:01:10,969
(Dark Hole)

652
01:01:11,510 --> 01:01:13,070
The black smoke...

653
01:01:13,170 --> 01:01:15,579
is watching us, not attacking us.

654
01:01:16,510 --> 01:01:19,809
So you must not trust people.
You should trust him.

655
01:01:19,880 --> 01:01:21,480
This is the mark of the chosen.

656
01:01:21,550 --> 01:01:23,449
Listen to me carefully.

657
01:01:23,619 --> 01:01:24,789
Watch out!

658
01:01:24,849 --> 01:01:27,519
Do you think you can run from them?

659
01:01:27,760 --> 01:01:30,590
You should go first, Detective.
You'll be in danger too.

660
01:01:30,889 --> 01:01:33,090
There's no time to block this! Let's go!
